## Security Baseline

Agents must follow these requirements for all changes:

- Validate all input on the server — never trust client-provided data
- Never trust client-provided identity, scope, or permissions
- Use Supabase RLS for row-level data isolation — every table needs a policy
- Store secrets in .env.local — never commit credentials or keys
- No secrets in logs, error messages, or API responses
- Enforce auth/authz explicitly on every API route
- Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY to the client
- Follow OWASP Top 10

