## Monitoring

- Health endpoint: GET /api/health → { status: "ok", version, timestamp }
- Error tracking: Sentry (SENTRY_DSN in environment)
- Uptime monitoring: Uptime Kuma polling /api/health every 60 seconds
- Alerts: Slack webhook (SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL in environment)

## Deployment

- Platform: Vercel
- Production: main branch → automatic deploy on push
- Preview: any other branch → automatic preview deployment
- Environment variables: set in Vercel dashboard (not committed to git)
- Database migrations: supabase/migrations/ — pushed via `supabase db push`

## Commit Conventions

- One commit per meaningful change (one feature, one fix, one refactor)
- Never commit .env.local or any file with real credentials
- Always run `npm run typecheck` before committing
- Commit AGENTS.md changes alongside the code changes they document
